element.name: Sidetracked - Skerries by Windsockers, Traditional Cache (1/1.5)

p.b: Skerries railway station is located on the main Dublin-Belfast Railway line.

long-description.p: The station was opened in 1844. The Great Northern Railway later added a number of other buildings to the original station following its takeover in 1876, these included the GNR signal cabin canopies, brick built goods shed complete with engineers siding and loop Skerries also has a subway, one of few at Irish stations.
Side-Tracked Caches are intended to provide quick Cache-and-dashes at Train Stations.
The Cache is a small micro container please rehide it well to prevent the many muggles from discovering it.
